#. Tag: refpurpose
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "Analyze return-addresses from dmalloc logfiles."
msgstr "Analysér returadresser fra dmalloc-logfiler."

#. Tag: cmdsynopsis
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>extend_dmalloc</command> <group><option><replaceable>dmalloc-log</"
"replaceable> <command>binary</command></option></group>"
msgstr ""
"<command>extend_dmalloc</command> <group><option><replaceable>dmalloc-logg</"
"replaceable> <command>binærfil</command></option></group>"

#. Tag: title
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Beskrivelse"

#. Tag: para
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>extend_dmalloc</command> will run <command>gdb</command>(1) to get "
"information on the return-addresses from a <command>dmalloc</command>(1) "
"logfile. Specifically it will examine any <literal>ra=</literal> lines and "
"try to get the corresponding line numbers"
msgstr ""
"<command>extend_dmalloc</command> kør <command>gdb</command>(1) for at få "
"information om returadresser fra en <command>dmalloc</command>(1) logfil. I "
"særdeleshed undersøger den alle linjer med <literal>ra=</literal> og "
"forsøger hente tilsvarende linjenummer."

#. Tag: para
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The argument <option><command>binary</command></option> must be the binary "
"that generated the log <filename>dmalloc-log</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Argumentet <option><command>binærfil</command></option> skal være den binære "
"fil som oprettede loggen <filename>dmalloc-logg</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "This utility is part of the &kde; Software Development Kit."
msgstr "Værktøjet er en del af &kde;'s programmeludviklingsmiljø."

#. Tag: title
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Notes"
msgstr "Noter"

#. Tag: para
#: man-extend_dmalloc.1.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may wish to direct the output from <command>extend_dmalloc</command> to "
"a file, since otherwise <command>gdb</command> seems to prompt for a return "
"as if you are at the end of a page."
msgstr ""
"Du bør måske sende udskrift fra <command>extend_dmalloc</command> til en "
"fil, eftersom <command>gdb</command> ellers synes at spørge efter et "
"returtegn, som om du er ved slutningen af en side."

